<title type="html"><![CDATA[10/5 Do you hate speaking English around native speakers / Introverts vs Extroverts (Host:Danny)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=82&amp;p=86#p86"><![CDATA[
<span style="font-weight: bold">Host : Danny</span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session 1.</span><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Do you hate speaking English around native speakers</span><br />Please find video as below.<br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lawHYX5eB20" class="postlink">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lawHYX5eB20</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussions:</span><br />1. Do you hate speaking English around native speakers? Are you sometimes getting stammer or losing words while you’re not when speaking with other non-native English learner? Why or why not?<br />2. In many occasion, some people look at native speaker as if they are up and better than them in anyway, what’s your opinion?<br />3. What were the longest conversations you have had with foreigner? How was that?<br />4. it’s not a test but a scenario imagination If you were asked by a foreigner in the airplane about how to make a tour to Taipei, can you do it in no time? If so, show us members how. If not, anything else we should add?<br />5. Share your now-the-best English learning methods or any textbooks, materials or resources that you can bring in to better our language skills.<br /><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session 2.</span><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Introverts vs Extroverts</span><br />Please find video as below.<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sfjN15zsPyQI</span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussions:</span><br />1. Are you an introvert , extrovert or just right in the middle, ambivert? How do you measure it?<br />2. Are there any advantage of being an introvert or extrovert? Which one is better? What are the downsides of them?<br />3. In many ways, our society has an extroversion bias that extroverts can do things much better then introverts, because we’re in a sociable society? What’s your opining? <br />4. Is it a stereotype or not that introverts are shy and unsociable? Contrary to the perspectives, introverts may even be better public speaking, according to the video .do you agree?<br />5. Do you know anything about your personality traits? Have you ever tried looking for jobs or finding a mate by that?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=49">josh</a> — Tue Oct 03, 2017 5:42 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
